               <p>I am a <rs id="t17841208-116-viclabel550" type="occupation">fishmonger</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t17841208-116-victim1160 t17841208-116-viclabel550"></join> in <placeName id="t17841208-116-crimeloc551">White-rose-court, Coleman-street</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t17841208-116-crimeloc551" type="placeName" value="White-rose-court, Coleman-street"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t17841208-116-crimeloc551" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t17841208-116-off548 t17841208-116-crimeloc551"></join>, on Sunday the 21st of November, my wife and me went to church in the morning, and left the prisoner, who is our <rs id="t17841208-116-deflabel552" type="occupation">servant</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t17841208-116-defend1158 t17841208-116-deflabel552"></join>, at home, she had lived with us about three weeks; when we returned about one, I found the door upon the single latch, the house stripped, and the prisoner gone; I found her afterwards at the Waggon and Horse, at Tottenham, she had some of my wife's things on; she took the constable to a house just by; where the property was.</p>
               <p>
                  <xptr type="pageFacsimile" doc="178412080149"></xptr>
            
